tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows hypoglycemia with low HbA1c, elevated creatinine, and mild hyperkalemia, suggesting possible renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, and abnormal urine appearance, indicating possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy, though diabetes control appears tight or overcorrected. Hemoglobin is elevated with low erythrocyte count, possibly due to hemoconcentration. Recommend clinical correlation for renal function, review of diabetes management, and further nephrological evaluation.
